\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs44 \cf0 Heat 2 teaspoons olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add the scallions and bell pepper and cook until they begin to soften, about 2 minutes. Cool slightly.\
Mix 1/2 cup panko, the egg and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/milk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 milk}} in a small bowl. In a medium bowl, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whisk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 whisk}} the Worcestershire sauce, mustard, lemon juice, Old Bay and hot sauce; fold in the crabmeat, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/panko/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 panko}} mixture, scallionbell pepper mixture, 1/4 teaspoon salt and a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pinch/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 pinch}} of pepper. Shape into 8 patties and refrigerate 30 minutes.\
Coat the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/crab/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 crab}} cakes with the remaining 1/2 cup panko. Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil in the skillet over medium-high heat. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mist/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Mist}} the crab cakes with cooking spray and cook, sprayed-side down, 3 to 4 minutes. Spray the tops, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/flip/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 flip}} and cook 3 to 4 more minutes. Serve with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lemon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lemon}} wedges.\
